<exercise checkit-seed="0019" checkit-slug="A2" checkit-title="Standard matrices">
  <statement>
    <ol>
      <li>Find the standard matrix for the linear transformation <m>S:\mathbb{R}^ 3  \to \mathbb{R}^ 3 </m> given by
              <me>S\left(  \left[\begin{array}{c}
x_{1} \\
x_{2} \\
x_{3}
\end{array}\right]  \right) =  \left[\begin{array}{c}
-5 \, x_{1} - 5 \, x_{2} + 7 \, x_{3} \\
x_{1} + 4 \, x_{2} - 4 \, x_{3} \\
-3 \, x_{1} - 4 \, x_{2} + 5 \, x_{3}
\end{array}\right] .</me></li>
      <li>Let <m>T:\mathbb{R}^ 3  \to \mathbb{R}^ 2 </m> be the linear transformation given by the standard matrix
              <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
-1 &amp; 6 &amp; 0 \\
-1 &amp; 5 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] .</me>
              Compute <m>T\left( \left[\begin{array}{c}
-8 \\
4 \\
2
\end{array}\right]  \right)</m>.
          </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
-5 &amp; -5 &amp; 7 \\
1 &amp; 4 &amp; -4 \\
-3 &amp; -4 &amp; 5
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me>T\left( \left[\begin{array}{c}
-8 \\
4 \\
2
\end{array}\right]  \right)= \left[\begin{array}{c}
32 \\
28
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

